# 🔗 Scalable URL Shortener

A URL shortener built with Django, designed to handle high traffic with caching, rate limiting, and asynchronous processing.

---
## 📌 Features
- URL shortening with unique short codes
- Fast redirection using Redis caching
- IP-based rate limiting to prevent abuse
- Asynchronous click tracking using Celery

## 🚀 Live Demo
https://urlshortener-prjs.onrender.com

## Swagger
https://urlshortener-prjs.onrender.com/swagger

Usage of swagger:
- create short_code for your url using /shorten/ method (rate limited to 10/min)
- Hit the /resolve/short_code method
- At the first request the server would fetch data from database 
- Second time the response would be faster, the data would be fetched from cache


---

## 🏗️ Architecture
        ┌───────────────┐
        │     User      │
        └──────┬────────┘
               │
               ▼
        ┌───────────────┐
        │   Django API  │
        │   (Gunicorn)  │
        └──────┬────────┘
               │
       ┌───────┴────────┐
       ▼                ▼
┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐
│ Redis Cache  │ │ PostgreSQL   │
│ (Hot Data)   │ │ (Persistent) │
└──────┬───────┘ └──────┬───────┘
       │                │
       └────────┬───────┘
                ▼
        ┌───────────────┐
        │ Celery Worker │
        │ (Async Tasks) │
        └───────────────┘

---

## ⚙️ Tech Stack

- Backend: Django, Django REST Framework  
- Cache & Broker: Redis  
- Async Processing: Celery  
- Database: PostgreSQL  
- Deployment: Docker / Render

---

## 🔌 API Endpoints

### Create Short URL
POST /api/shorten/

Request:
{
  "original_url": "https://example.com"
}

Response:
{
  "short_code": "abc123,
  "original_url": "https://example.com",
  "short_url": "https://your-app.com/abc123"
}

---

### Redirect
GET /<short_code>/

Redirects to original URL

---

## 🧠 Key Design Decisions

- Used cache-aside pattern for reducing DB load
- Implemented rate limiting using Redis to handle abuse
- Offloaded analytics to Celery to reduce API latency

---

## 📈 Performance Optimizations

- Reduced latency using Redis caching
- Indexed short_code for faster lookups
- Async processing for non-blocking requests

---

## 🚧 Future Improvements

- Token bucket rate limiting
- Distributed caching
- Click analytics dashboard
